column1: #Text=Zalalövő is a town in Zala County in the valley of Zala river .
#Text=The Roman legions created a military camp on the northern shore of the Zala river at the beginning of the 1st century .
#Text=Around the camp a village-like settlement founded .
#Text=In 124 , Emperor Hadrian gave town status for the settlement , and called as Municipium Aelium Salla .
#Text=However , in the middle of the 2nd century the invading Germanic tribes destroyed the settlement .
#Text=According to a 13th-century document , royal archers lived here .
#Text=Zalalövő was elevated to town status in 2000 .
#Text=This article includes travel-related information not only for Zalalövő , but also for the surrounding rural areas .
#Text=Direct trains are available once a day from Budapest -Déli pályaudvar via Székesfehérvár , Veszprém and Zalaegerszeg .
#Text=The journey takes 4 hours and costs 4840 Ft.
#Text=Toward east : Zalaegerszeg seven times a day .
#Text=The journey takes about 30 minutes and costs 465 Ft.
#Text=Toward west : Őriszentpéter seven times a day .
#Text=The journey takes about 15 minutes and costs 310 Ft. There are direct international trains via Bajánsenye to Hodoš ( Slovenia ) four times a day , and to Ljubljana once a day .
#Text=There is no ticket office , tickets can be purchased on the train .
#Text=The train station is just 700 m away from the center .
#Text=The journey takes about 30 minutes and costs 465 Ft. From Budapest -Népliget , you have to transfer in Zalaegerszeg .
#Text=The whole journey from Budapest takes 4 hours and costs 4770 Ft.
#Text=There is no local public transport or taxi service .
#Text=You can use the regional buses operated by ÉNYKK .
